Option 1: Edit the MySQL configration file (my.cnf)
  - using putty communicate with your server
  - find where is my.cnf using find command
  
  #sudo find / -name my.cnf
  Mostly my.cnf is in /etc/mysql
  - use text editor insert default time zone i.e. for Bangkok +07:00
  
  #sudo nano /etc/mysql/my.cnf
  
  Scroll down to the bottom and add :
  [mysqld]
  default-time-zone = "+07:00"
  Then restart MySQL
  
  #sudo service mysql restart
  
  Done.
  
